author: The Current
description:
Watch Matthew Caws' outdoor performance recorded at The Current's Happy Hours
Support The Current: https://support.mpr.org/youtube  

Nada Surf’s frontman Matthew Caws played a career-spanning set at Surly Brewing Co. in Minneapolis on Thursday, Sept. 19, 2024. The event, hosted by The Current’s Jessica Paxton, was the finale for The Current’s 2024 Happy Hours series. The 2025 Happy Hours series has been announced; find that schedule at https://www.thecurrent.org/happyhours 

Watch Matthew Caws perform a solo acoustic performance of "Open Seas," recorded outside Surly in Minneapolis last September. You can also find photos from the day posted here: https://www.thecurrent.org/feature/2024/09/20/photos-matthew-caws-of-nada-surf-plays-acoustic-set-at-surly 

Musician
Matthew Caws of @nadasurf

To celebrate The Current’s 20th Anniversary, The Current’s Live Sessions Vault unlocks never-before-seen live performance videos of bands and artists who have played in our iconic studio. 

Watch to see the full session of Maggie Rogers, featuring previously unreleased footage, from when they visited The Current studio back in 2017.
